x^2y''-3xy'+3y=0
y'(1)=6, y(1)=4
y = x^m \implies y' = m x^{m-1} \implies y'' = m(m-1)x^{m-2}
\qquad \qquad \qquad \qquad y(x) = x(x^2 + 3)
ax^2u''+bxu'+cu=0
D=x\frac{d}{dx}
ax^2u''+bxu'+cu=aD^2u+(b-a)Du+cu.
aD^2+(b-a)D+c
u
aD^2+(b-a)D+c=\alpha(D-\beta)(D-\gamma)
xu'=\gamma u
\beta\neq\gamma
(D-\beta)(D-\gamma)u=0.
(D-\gamma)u=0
(D-\beta)u=0.
am^2+(b-a)m+c=0\\ m^2-4m+3=0\\ (m-3)(m-1)=0\\ m_1=3, \, m_2=1\\ m_1 \neq m_2 \text{ so}\\ Y=C_1X^3+C_2X^1   \text{ is general solution}
